### Parity Problem

The Rust frontend currently **requires an exact version match** (`"0.1.0"`), but:
- The Go and TypeScript frontends only require major.minor match (so `"0.1.X"` would pass)
- The core engine checks major.minor compatibility using the `major_minor()` function
- This creates an incompatibility: if patch version advances to `"0.1.1"`, the Rust frontend will reject it while others accept it

